flowRoot.flowPara: Shift the bits to the left of the preceding token, resulting in the transformations shown in the table on the left.
e.g. A<<
Shift the bits to the right of the preceding token, resulting in the transformations shown in the table on the left.
e.g. A>>
Copies the previous register address into an opponents core at the same register address
e.g. A^^
Assigns the previous numeric token to the subsequent register
e.g. 7 > A
Swaps the previous register from the player's core into the subsequent register of an opponents core
e.g. A B
Copies the previous register address from an opponents core to the player's core at the same register address
e.g. A
Protects the previous register for the number of cycles of the subsequent numeric token, or 1 if no subsequent numeric token
e.g. A or A 4
Transfers the previous register address from the players core to the output, wiping the register
Transfers the sum of all the registers into the output, wiping all registers and creating a NOP for the next cycle
Clears the preceding register in an opponents core
e.g. A<>
Copies sums either the preceding numeric token or register with the subsequent register and assigns the result to that register
e.g. 7><A or B><C
